-- Morgan Stanley, StanChart picked to manage India share sales -sources
-- By Sumeet Chatterjee and Devidutta Tripathy
-- Fri Sep 26, 2014 09:59AM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, Sept 26 (Reuters) - Morgan Stanley <MS.N> and Standard Chartered <STAN.L> are among six banks picked to manage the sales of shares in two state-run Indian companies, sources directly involved in the deals said on Friday.

The combined sales, worth about $470 million at current market values, are part of government plans for a record $10.5 billion in asset sales in the year to March to help plug a budget deficit. [ID:nL3N0R23VT] Morgan Stanley and Indian banks JM Financial <JMSH.NS> and Avendus have been selected to manage the sale of shares in state-run Rural Electrification Corp <RURL.NS>, the sources said.